This directory contains codes for STMAS 4D analysis in a sigma height coordinate

Prepared by Yuanfu Xie Dec. 2009 at Global Systems Division, ESRL/NOAA.

This is a redesigned of stmas developed by Wei Li, Zhongjie He and Yuanfu Xie with
options of full dynamic model constraints and MPI.

Development team:
Brad Beechler
Jenny Hui
Dong Li
Yuanfu Xie

For vertical coordinate, we choose sigma-height:

sigma = (h-h_s)/(h_t - h_s)*h_t

where h_s is the surface height, terrain following and h_t is the domain height.

